# Walkthrough - Unique IDs & HBV Bug Fix

I have implemented unique IDs for all form fields in [legacy_schedule.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html) and resolved the bug where "HBV" was incorrectly printed in the PDF.

## Changes Made

### 1. Unique ID Implementation
Every input field (checkboxes, radio buttons, text inputs) in the [legacy_schedule.html](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html) form has been assigned a unique ID following a consistent naming convention:
- `chk_section_subitem` for checkboxes and radio buttons.
- `txt_section_subitem` for text inputs.
- `sel_section_subitem` for select dropdowns.

This improves the reliability of element selection in JavaScript and facilitates future automated testing.

### 2. Improved [isChecked](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/index.html#3177-3194) Function
The [isChecked](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/index.html#3177-3194) function was updated to be more robust:
- **ID Support**: It now primarily looks for elements by ID, which is the most reliable method.
- **Improved Specificity**: When searching by keyword, it now selects the most specific element (shortest text match). This prevents parent elements from being incorrectly identified as the target when they contain sub-items with matching text.

```javascript
function isChecked(idOrKeyword) {
    // 1. Try by ID first
    const elById = document.getElementById(idOrKeyword);
    if (elById && (elById.type === 'checkbox' || elById.type === 'radio')) {
        return elById.checked;
    }

    // 2. Fallback to keyword search (refined for specificity)
    const elements = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('li, label, span.bold-item'));
    const candidates = elements.filter(el => el.textContent.includes(idOrKeyword));
    
    if (candidates.length > 0) {
        candidates.sort((a, b) => a.textContent.length - b.textContent.length);
        const target = candidates[0].closest('li, label');
        if (target) {
            const cb = target.querySelector('input[type="checkbox"], input[type="radio"]');
            if (cb && cb.checked) return true;
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```

### 3. HBV Printing Bug Fix
The PDF generation logic for the Hepatitis section was rewritten to:
- Use the new unique IDs (`chk_dig_carrier_hbv`, `chk_dig_carrier_hcv`, `chk_dig_cirrh`).
- Use properly scoped local variables (`let hNote`, `let hExtras`) to prevent global scope pollution.
- Correctly check only the intended checkboxes.

```javascript
// "Hepatitis"
let hNote = "";
let hExtras = [];
if (isChecked("chk_dig_carrier_hbv")) hExtras.push("HBV");
if (isChecked("chk_dig_carrier_hcv")) hExtras.push("HCV");
if (isChecked("chk_dig_cirrh")) hExtras.push("Cirrhosis");
if (hExtras.length > 0) hNote = hExtras.join(", ");
if (hNote) draw(hNote, 250.19, 545.0 + 2);
checkPhItem("Hepatitis", hNote.length > 0);
```

### 4. Nested Sub-item Extraction Fix
A bug where unselected sibling items (like "Right" when "Left" was checked for Hemiparesis) appeared in the summary has been fixed by:
- **Standardizing HTML Structure**: Affected sections (Hemiparesis, Atrial fibrillation, AV Block, Bronchoscope options) were converted from in-line labels to hierarchical `<ul>` structures.
- **Refining [getCleanText](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/index.html#3334-3341)**: Updated the text extraction helper to explicitly ignore nested `<label>` tags, preventing parent labels from capturing child text nodes.

### 7. Patient Header Redesign & Dynamic Duration Logic
The patient detail view header has been refined to ensure data accuracy, better labeling, and real-time performance tracking:
- **Refined Labels**: Updated labels for clarity:
    - `麻醉方式/時間` -> `麻醉方式/耗時`
    - `手術備註` -> `醫師備註`
- **Dynamic Duration Logic**:
    - **Estimated Duration**: Uses **`OROPMIN`** as the primary source for planned surgery time (length only).
    - **Actual Duration Tracking**: Prioritizes actual duration calculated from anesthesia start/end times (**`ANEBGNDTTM`** and **`ANEENDDTTM`**) for accuracy.
    - **Performance Visualization**:
        - Shows planned length for unfinished surgeries: [([120])](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html#4261-4264).
        - Shows planned vs. actual for finished surgeries: [([120 / 110])](file:///c:/Users/A03772/.gemini/antigravity/Combined_Server/SurgerySchedule/templates/legacy_schedule.html#4261-4264). (Removed start time as requested).
        - **Color Coding**: Applies **light green** (`#d1ffcd`) if faster than planned, and **light red** (`#ffd1d1`) if slower.
- **Physician Memo**: Now prioritized from **`ORDERMEMO` / `UDOINSTRUCTION`** in the surgery order (finding "Synthes"), with a fallback to `PAT_ADM_DRMEMO`.
- **Improved Hierarchy**: Main demographics (Name, ID, Age/Sex) remain primary, with procedural details and performance metrics as secondary gray metadata (or color-coded metrics).

